<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1437,1591,1977]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Karyotype: 2n = 64 and FN = 66. Autosomal complement: one large submetacentric pair, one small metacentric pair, and 29 acrocentric pairs medium to small decreasing in size. Sex chromosomes: X, a medium subtelocentric; Y chromosome presented two different morphologies, a small metacentric, and a small acrocentric (
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L." pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref67114" refString="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L. (1976) Karyotypic variation in Oryzomyine rodents (Cricetinae) with comments on chromosomal evolution in the Neotropical Cricetine complex. Occasional papers of the Museum of Zoology, 49, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1976">Gardner &amp; Patton 1976</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 8, 
<figureCitation box="[337,425,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1037,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-431@13.[151,1436,1029,1925]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Euryoryzomys. (■) E. emmonsae; (□) E. lamia; (▲) E. macconnelli; (○) E. nitidus; (l) E. russatus; (r) Euryoryzomys sp. nov.; (ê) Euryoryzomys sp.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423621/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Aniskin, V. M. &amp; Volobouev, V. T." box="[436,750,1735,1761]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="557 - 562" refId="ref63990" refString="Aniskin, V. M. &amp; Volobouev, V. T. (1999) Comparative chromosome banding of two South-American species of rice rats of the genus Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae). Chromosome Research, 7, 557 - 562. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1009245729902" type="journal article" year="1999">Aniskin &amp; Volobouev 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Patton, J. L. &amp; Silva, M. N. &amp; Malcolm, J. R." box="[762,967,1735,1761]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 306" refId="ref71077" refString="Patton, J. L., Silva, M. N. &amp; Malcolm, J. R. (2000) Mammals of the Rio Jurua and the evolutionary and ecological diversification of Amazonia. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 244, 1 - 306. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 244 % 3 C 0001: MOTRJA % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">
Patton 
<emphasis box="[842,892,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
). Another fundamental number of 64 was reported for a sample from 
<collectingRegion box="[457,604,1771,1797]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, state of 
<collectingCountry box="[703,774,1771,1797]" name="Brazil" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, due to the presence of one large acrocentric pair instead of a submetacentric one (
<bibRefCitation author="Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Ventura, K. &amp; Ferguson-Smith, M. A. &amp; O'Brien, P. C. M. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[399,621,1806,1833]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="0117579" refId="ref66405" refString="Di-Nizo, C. B., Ventura, K., Ferguson-Smith, M. A., O'Brien, P. C. M., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2015) Comparative chromosome painting in six species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) and the karyotype evolution of the genus. Public Library of Science one, 10 (2), e 0117579. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0117579" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di-Nizo 
<emphasis box="[499,547,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). C-banding metaphases exhibited blocks of constitutive heterochromatin on the pericentromeric region of the autosomal pairs, with the exception of one the large submetacentric pair and five acrocentric pairs of medium-sized. The X chromosome presented the short arm entirely heterochromatic. The metacentric Y chromosome was entirely heterochromatic (
<bibRefCitation author="Aniskin, V. M. &amp; Volobouev, V. T." box="[816,1135,1915,1941]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="557 - 562" refId="ref63990" refString="Aniskin, V. M. &amp; Volobouev, V. T. (1999) Comparative chromosome banding of two South-American species of rice rats of the genus Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae). Chromosome Research, 7, 557 - 562. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1009245729902" type="journal article" year="1999">Aniskin &amp; Volobouev 1999</bibRefCitation>
). G-banding was also performed (
<bibRefCitation author="Aniskin, V. M. &amp; Volobouev, V. T." box="[246,559,1951,1977]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="557 - 562" refId="ref63990" refString="Aniskin, V. M. &amp; Volobouev, V. T. (1999) Comparative chromosome banding of two South-American species of rice rats of the genus Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae). Chromosome Research, 7, 557 - 562. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1009245729902" type="journal article" year="1999">Aniskin &amp; Volobouev 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Ventura, K. &amp; Ferguson-Smith, M. A. &amp; O'Brien, P. C. M. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[571,794,1950,1977]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="0117579" refId="ref66405" refString="Di-Nizo, C. B., Ventura, K., Ferguson-Smith, M. A., O'Brien, P. C. M., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2015) Comparative chromosome painting in six species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) and the karyotype evolution of the genus. Public Library of Science one, 10 (2), e 0117579. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0117579" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di-Nizo 
<emphasis box="[670,719,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
